# README Documentation Standards

## Required Structure (In Order)

### 1. Project Title & Badges

- Clear, descriptive project name
- Include relevant badges (version, build status, license, etc.)
- Example: `# Project Name [![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.0.0-blue.svg)]`

### 2. Business Description

- 2-3 sentences explaining what the project does in business/user terms
- **Not** technical implementation details
- Answer: **Why it exists?**, **what problem it solves?** and **Who benefits?**

### 3. Tech Stack

- Bulleted list of key technologies
- Include versions if version-specific (e.g., "Node.js 18+", "React 18.2.0")

### 4. Installation

```bash
# Include exact install command
pnpm install
```

### 5. Configuration

#### Environment Variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

```env
# List REQUIRED variables with example values
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
API_KEY=your_key_here
PORT=3000
```

#### Port Configuration

- Specify default port: `PORT=3000`
- Document port customization if applicable

### 6. Getting Started

#### Essential Commands

```bash
# Development
pnpm run dev

# Build
pnpm run build

# Tests
pnpm test

# Database Migrations (if applicable)
pnpm run migrate
```

### 7. Dependencies

#### External Services

- Database (PostgreSQL, MongoDB, etc.) (if applicable)
- Messaging platforms (Redis, RabbitMQ, etc.) (if applicable)
- Required external APIs (if applicable)

### 8. Project Structure

```plaintext
src/
├── components/     # React/Vue components
├── services/      # API calls and external services
├── utils/         # Helper functions
└── ...
```

### 9. Contributing

- Link to CONTRIBUTING.md or brief guidelines
- Code style references

### 10. License

- License type (MIT, Apache 2.0, etc.)
- Copyright notice if required

## Documentation Guidelines

### Writing Standards

- Use clear, simple language (avoid jargon)
- Include **code examples** for complex operations
- Add **screenshots/diagrams** for UI components
- Keep updated with code changes

